<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-45-0996 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper describes a generic message translator that enables a computeruser without programming knowledge to specify a program for translatingbetween two different computer-based message systems. Thus messages formattedfor use in one system can be automatically translated by the computerinto the proper format for use in the other system. The computer userworks interactively with the computer to specify the translating program,making use of the appropriate visual paradigms for the message structure.13 refs., 5 figs.</TEXT></DOC>